	(345,5,'2015-09-14 07:47:57','2015-09-14 07:47:57','Incredible lineup of Zen-inspired mobile, lifestyle and home computing products, plus brand-new gaming products from Republic of Gamers\r\n\r\nBerlin, Germany (2nd September, 2015) — ASUS Chairman Jonney Shih today revealed details of the company’s latest innovations in mobile, wearable and home computing technology, plus the latest gaming innovations from ASUS Republic of Gamers (ROG), in a pre-IFA 2015 press event held at the Bolle Meierei, in Berlin, Germany.\r\n\r\nNew products announced included RT-AC5300, the world’s fastest Wi-Fi router, and VivoStick PC, a slim and stylish ultra-miniature Windows 10 ‘stick’ PC. The latest ZenFone lineup, including the new ZenFone Zoom model, was introduced to Europe, along with the announcement of pricing and availability for ZenWatch 2 and the latest models in the ZenPad and Zen AiO families.\r\n\r\nFeaturing in the incredible lineup were the G752 gaming laptop, ROG Maximus VIII Extreme/Assembly, ROG Matrix 980Ti, ROG Swift PG348Q, ROG 7.1 headset, and ROG G20 Special Edition. The 165Hz ROG Swift PG279Q gaming monitor was also showcased. Before leaving the stage, Mr. Shih surprised the audience with a sneak preview of GX700, the world’s first water-cooled gaming laptop.\r\n\r\n“We are incredibly proud to offer our customers the incredible Zen experience by achieving the perfect balance between beauty and strength,” said Mr. Shih. “Today\'s lineup of Zen-inspired products not only provide the most intuitive user experiences, but also deliver empowering luxury for everyone to enjoy.”\r\n\r\nJoining Mr. Shih on stage, Intel’s Senior Vice President and General Manager of Client Computing Group, Kirk Skaugen, spoke about the successful collaboration between ASUS and Intel® on these brand new mobile and computing devices. “ASUS and Intel have been working closely together for almost three decades to bring the best experience possible to consumers with the latest technology innovation,” said Mr. Skaugen. “We are excited to have worked with ASUS on their incredible new products – from all-in-ones and gaming laptops based on the new 6th-generation Intel Core processor to compute sticks, tablets and smartphones based on the Intel Atom processor. Intel technologies bring great performance, immersive experiences, long battery life and slim form factors across a range of beautiful ASUS devices.”\r\n\r\nZenWatch 2 is a remarkable evolution of the original ZenWatch, with an incredible 2-day battery life and a choice of 2 sizes, 3 case colors and 18 strap options.\r\n\r\nZenPad S 8.0, ZenPad 8.0 and ZenPad 10 are elegant and powerful Android™ tablets. They pioneer many world-first technology innovations including built-in DTS-HD Premium Sound™, and interchangeable covers for ZenPad 8.0, including an Audio Cover that adds 6-speaker, 5.1-channel surround sound.\r\n\r\nZen AiO S is a stunningly-beautiful, high-performance all-in-one PC that fuses art with the latest technology to create a true masterpiece for the home or office.\r\n\r\nRT-AC5300 is an ultra-fast tri-band 802.11ac router capable of combined total speeds of up to 5334Mbit/s, with supreme coverage and stability.\r\n\r\nThe revolutionary VivoStick PC is an ultra-miniature PC that turns any HDMI-enabled TV or monitor into a fully-functional Windows 10 PC, and which can be controlled remotely from a smartphone.\r\n\r\nThe groundbreaking ZenFone Zoom is the world’s thinnest smartphone to feature a camera with a 3X optical zoom capability.\r\n\r\nAll new Zen and ROG products will be on display at our Sales and Media Lounge located at Berliner Freiheit 2. The Lounge will be open from 3rd-4th September and 7th-8th September from 9am – 7pm (except on September 7th, when the Lounge will open at 11am).\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nZenWatch 2: Time-honored craftsmanship, infinite style\r\n\r\nZenWatch 2 is a stylish and personalized wearable device powered by Android Wear and produced in partnership with Google